## Next Iteration Details (Multi-page & Booking)

1. **Routing Setup**: Added `react-router-dom` to support a multi-page structure.
2. **New Header**: Created [Header.jsx](file:///c:/Users/baben/Desktop/TAXI/src/components/Header.jsx) featuring a top bar with WhatsApp, Telegram, Max, and Phone contacts. Includes smooth scroll navigation across pages.
3. **Hero Booking Form**: Replaced the simple CTA button in [Hero.jsx](file:///c:/Users/baben/Desktop/TAXI/src/components/Hero.jsx) with a comprehensive glassmorphism booking form (Откуда, Куда, Дата, Класс, Данные клиента). Added **Эконом** and **Стандарт** to the car classes dropdown.
4. **Routes Pages for SEO**:
   - [RoutesPreview.jsx](file:///c:/Users/baben/Desktop/TAXI/src/components/RoutesPreview.jsx): This standalone section was removed from the home page. The **sleek, animated text marquee** showing popular routes was shrunk and relocated neatly below the contact forms in the Hero section.
   - [RoutesPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/baben/Desktop/TAXI/src/pages/RoutesPage.jsx): Created a dedicated `/routes` SEO page with an elegant grid of route cards. Removed the 'price from' tag per request.
5. **Fleet Updates**:
   - Completely migrated the previous custom Framer-Motion drag mechanics to **`Swiper` React Library** ([Services.jsx](file:///c:/Users/baben/Desktop/TAXI/src/components/Services.jsx)). The layout responds perfectly to native dragging with the Navigation controls and integrated **pagination dots**, rigidly snapping by groups (4 cards on desktop, 1 on mobile). The drag physics now emulate a native mobile app layout perfectly.
   - Correctly categorized the VW Transporter, Toyota Alphard, and Kia Carnival into the **Минивэн** class alongside the Mercedes Vito.
   - Completely populated the fleet list with the **20 requested vehicles**. All vehicles are now using actual custom images.
   - Replaced Chery Tiggo with **Nissan Teana** per user request.
   - **Standardized image sizing**: All car images are strictly forced to `200x120px` with `object-contain` and a drop shadow, ensuring visual uniformity regardless of original proportions.
   - Each card features a bright class badge, an isolated car image, and an accurate specs section highlighting specific details.

